# 🚀 SaaS Invoice & Business Management Backend

A production-ready **multi-tenant SaaS backend system** built with Django and Django REST Framework.
This project manages **invoices, clients, expenses, notifications, and user management**, similar to real-world business SaaS platforms.

---

## 🔥 Key Features

### 🔐 Authentication & Security

* JWT Authentication (Access & Refresh Tokens)
* User Registration & Login
* Password Reset System
* User Activation / Deactivation

---

### 👥 User & Tenant Management

* Multi-tenant architecture (multiple businesses support)
* Add / Remove Users
* Role & Status Management
* Tenant Profile Management
* Company Logo Upload

---

### 🧾 Invoice Management

* Create, Update, Delete Invoices
* Invoice PDF Generation
* Last Invoice Tracking
* Invoice Status Breakdown (analytics)

---

### 🧑‍💼 Client Management

* Add / View / Update Clients
* Client Detail View

---

### 💸 Expense Management

* Create Expenses
* Approve / Reject Expense Requests
* Expense Tracking

---

### 📊 Dashboard & Analytics

* Business Dashboard Overview
* Monthly Income vs Expense
* Invoice Status Breakdown
* User-specific Dashboard

---

### 🔔 Notifications System

* User Notifications
* Unread Notification Count

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

* Python
* Django
* Django REST Framework
* JWT Authentication
* PostgreSQL / SQLite
* Pipenv (dependency management)

---

## 📡 API Endpoints

### 🔐 Authentication

* `POST /api/token/` → Obtain JWT token
* `POST /api/token/refresh/` → Refresh token
* `POST /api/users/register/` → Register user
* `POST /api/users/login/` → Login user

---

### 👥 User Management

* `POST /api/users/add-user/`
* `GET /api/users/user-list/`
* `GET /api/users/profile/`
* `DELETE /api/users/delete-user/{id}/`
* `PATCH /api/users/toggle-user-status/{id}/`
* `POST /api/users/reset-password/{id}/`

---

### 🏢 Tenant Management

* `GET /api/users/tenant-info/`
* `POST /api/users/tenant/upload-logo/`
* `PUT /api/users/tenant/update/`

---

### 🧑‍💼 Clients

* `GET /api/users/clients/`
* `GET /api/users/clients/{id}/`

---

### 🧾 Invoices

* `GET /api/users/invoices/`
* `POST /api/users/invoices/manage/`
* `GET /api/users/invoices/{id}/`
* `GET /api/users/invoices/{id}/pdf/`
* `GET /api/users/invoices/last/`

---

### 💸 Expenses

* `GET /api/users/expenses/`
* `POST /api/users/expenses/`
* `GET /api/users/expenses/{id}/`
* `POST /api/users/expenses/{id}/approve-reject/`

---

### 📊 Dashboard & Analytics

* `GET /api/users/dashboard/`
* `GET /api/users/user-dashboard/`
* `GET /api/users/monthly-income-expense/`
* `GET /api/users/invoice-status-breakdown/`

---

### 🔔 Notifications

* `GET /api/users/notifications/`
* `GET /api/users/notifications/unread-count/`

---

### ⚙️ Utility APIs

* `POST /api/users/check-username/`
* `POST /api/users/check-email/`
* `POST /api/users/check-tenant/`

---

## ⚙️ Installation & Setup (Pipenv)

```bash id="setup_pipenv"
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/mujibsani/saas_invoice_backend.git

# Move into project directory
cd saas_invoice_backend

# Install dependencies
pipenv install

# Activate virtual environment
pipenv shell

# Run database migrations
python manage.py migrate

# Start development server
python manage.py runserver
```

---

## 🔐 Authentication Usage

Include JWT token in request headers:

```bash id="auth_header"
Authorization: Bearer <your_access_token>
```

---

## 📂 Media Handling

Uploaded files (logos, invoices PDFs, etc.) are served via:

```
/media/<file_path>
```

